1
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:39,359
A person

2
00:01:40,319 --> 00:01:41,560
Has to stand tall, right?

3
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:44,319
Why are you telling me this?

4
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:45,680
What's the point?

5
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:48,000
Because we all swore an oath

6
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:49,959
This blood in our veins

7
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:52,640
is meant to be shed on this land

8
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:53,439
What blood?

9
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:56,280
My blood dried up long ago

10
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,599
Give me a straight answer

11
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,879
What we said before

12
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,840
Does it still count?

13
00:02:04,439 --> 00:02:05,560
What did we say back then?

14
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:06,480
We said too much

15
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,039
Just treat it as nonsense

16
00:02:12,919 --> 00:02:13,719
Tang Deyuan

17
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,159
Is that something a person should say?

18
00:02:17,479 --> 00:02:18,479
Back in the labor camp

19
00:02:18,479 --> 00:02:19,360
We made a promise

20
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,120
You'd drive to pick us up

21
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:22,199
But where were you?

22
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,479
I still haven't settled that score with you

23
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:25,800
All these years

24
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,439
Me, Yunhu, and the Squad Leader

25
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,479
We thought about you every day

26
00:02:31,159 --> 00:02:32,680
Didn't know if you were alive or dead

27
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:34,960
Today, the Squad Leader

28
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:36,520
took a huge risk

29
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,120
to come see you

30
00:02:37,759 --> 00:02:38,919
And now that we meet

31
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:40,360
this is what you say

32
00:02:43,599 --> 00:02:46,120
Times have changed

33
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:47,800
You're right

34
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:49,800
Times are different now

35
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,000
The situation now

36
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,520
is really not like before

37
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,479
What's different?

38
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:54,319
What do you mean?

39
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,599
This place

40
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,000
isn't ruled by the Japanese anymore

41
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,080
Old Tang

42
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,000
The Japanese

43
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,319
won't last much longer

44
00:03:00,439 --> 00:03:01,360
Come on, give me a break

45
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,159
We've said that for years

46
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,319
So many have died

47
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,080
What did we get in return?

48
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:10,680
At least we're still alive

49
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,159
Around us

50
00:03:12,159 --> 00:03:13,719
so many comrades' blood debts

51
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,360
We have to settle them

52
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:16,599
I want to, but how?

53
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:17,599
Can we ever settle them all?

54
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,400
This time

55
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:20,879
We'll settle them all together

56
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:21,960
If you trust me

57
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,120
I trust you

58
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,719
But how can I trust you?

59
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,400
Even now, you guys

60
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,639
won't tell me the truth

61
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:39,319
Fine

62
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,520
I'll give you the truth

63
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:48,639
Our unit is still together

64
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:51,759
In Songlin Town, those two didn't wait for you

65
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:52,759
They waited for me

66
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,439
Except for you

67
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,080
Xiao Gui and Xiao Hua

68
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:57,159
The three of us

69
00:03:57,719 --> 00:03:59,599
crossed the river to the Soviet Union together

70
00:04:01,319 --> 00:04:02,199
We

71
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,520
are what you called

72
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:08,360
the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army Teaching Brigade

73
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:20,040
You're really not afraid.

74
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,160
That I might betray you?

75
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,720
If we dared to come, we're not afraid.

76
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:25,920
Besides,

77
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:26,800
just now you even

78
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,480
called me Squad Leader.

79
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:30,800
Deyuan,

80
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,120
I can tell

81
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,279
your conscience is still intact.

82
00:04:35,639 --> 00:04:37,000
You're still a Chinese.

83
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,519
A Chinese.

84
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:42,000
In this place,

85
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,319
how many Chinese are left?

86
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:44,560
How can you say there aren't any?

87
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,759
Open your eyes and look.

88
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:48,959
All those walking in the streets,

89
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:49,600
aren't they Chinese?

90
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,319
Those hiding in the woods,

91
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:52,399
fighting the Japanese,

92
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:53,120
aren't they Chinese?

93
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,680
Datouzi Ridge, the labor camp,

94
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,279
on the northern slope, hanging from the cliff branches,

95
00:04:57,279 --> 00:04:58,600
those hanging there, aren't they Chinese?

96
00:04:59,439 --> 00:05:00,879
And those buried in the mass grave,

97
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,879
When you say these things,

98
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:03,560
can you face

99
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,639
those who have passed, above and below?

100
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,000
Yes.

101
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,480
They were Chinese.

102
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,120
But they're all dead.

103
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,399
So many Chinese have died.

104
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:13,680
How many are still alive?

105
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,839
My life may not be worth much,

106
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,480
but surviving till now wasn't easy.

107
00:05:20,199 --> 00:05:21,279
What I need to do now

108
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,720
is to be true to myself,

109
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,240
and to my family.

110
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,600
Deyuan,

111
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:35,519
the Soviets have already reached

112
00:05:35,519 --> 00:05:37,000
the Germans' homeland.

113
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,399
The Japanese in the Pacific

114
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,120
are being beaten

115
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,000
so hard by the Americans they can't breathe.

116
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:44,920
The fascists are finished.

117
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:47,240
Northeast China will soon be liberated.

118
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,040
I'm not interested in all that.

119
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,079
It's too far from me.

120
00:05:52,639 --> 00:05:53,120
Fine.

121
00:05:54,199 --> 00:05:55,480
Let's talk about something closer.

122
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,920
The situation in the country now

123
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,720
is very different from before.

124
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,079
The Japanese in the pass

125
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,879
are being beaten badly by us.

126
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,639
We've been bullied for so long,

127
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,240
finally we see the dawn.

128
00:06:09,519 --> 00:06:11,480
Before, the Japanese were strong and we were weak.

129
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,000
Now it's our turn to stand up.

130
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:15,279
It's time to fight them.

131
00:06:15,879 --> 00:06:16,240
That's right.

132
00:06:17,160 --> 00:06:18,319
The time and place are right,

133
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:19,720
we just need the people.

134
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:21,839
We're here to find you.

135
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:23,920
Don't blame me for not

136
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,040
telling you the truth these days.

137
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,560
You should know

138
00:06:27,639 --> 00:06:28,439
we have discipline.

139
00:06:30,199 --> 00:06:30,800
That's good.

140
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,439
Discipline is a good thing.

141
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,279
Don't tell me anything.

142
00:06:35,439 --> 00:06:36,480
I don't want to hear it.

143
00:06:36,959 --> 00:06:37,639
Sit down.

144
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:38,439
What are you doing?

145
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:39,959
You won't listen to anything now, huh?

146
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:40,800
Nothing gets through to you.

147
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:41,399
Old Tang,

148
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:42,680
how did you end up like this?

149
00:06:43,639 --> 00:06:44,199
Let me tell you,

150
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:45,360
if you trust us,

151
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,160
this time we can really make it.

152
00:06:52,639 --> 00:06:54,360
Let me make myself clear.

153
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,439
Even if you manage to break in,

154
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:58,480
it'll be over a million bodies paving the way.

155
00:06:58,839 --> 00:06:59,959
That's exactly why,

156
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,240
we need you most right now.

157
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:03,399
Me?

158
00:07:08,199 --> 00:07:09,079
Hurry up and eat.

159
00:07:10,199 --> 00:07:11,240
This meal is on me.

160
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:13,360
Leave as soon as you're done.

161
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:14,600
Don't come back.

162
00:07:15,079 --> 00:07:16,480
I'll pretend I never saw you.

163
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:17,759
Alright.

164
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:20,199
While my heart hasn't turned cold yet.

165
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,519
Stop right there.

166
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,720
What are you doing?

167
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:24,800
What do you think I'm doing?

168
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,079
Boss.

169
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:28,800
What's wrong?

170
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:30,240
There's a fight at the door.

171
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,120
You'd better go check it out.

172
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,120
Who is it?

173
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:34,319
A beggar.

174
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,160
He stole a roast chicken from our shop.

175
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:37,759
They're about to beat him to death.

176
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,560
You filthy beggar!

177
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,480
How dare you steal a roast chicken!

178
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,399
That's what you get for stealing!

179
00:07:47,519 --> 00:07:48,240
Do you know how much chicken

180
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,319
costs per half a kilogram now?

181
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,120
You dare steal from here?

182
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,680
Do you know whose shop this is?

183
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,720
That's what you get for stealing!

184
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:54,319
Hit him harder!

185
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,199
That's what you get for stealing!

186
00:07:55,319 --> 00:07:55,839
That's what you get!

187
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,199
What are you doing?

188
00:07:59,040 --> 00:07:59,519
Er Ye.

189
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:01,000
Sorry to trouble you, sir.

190
00:08:02,879 --> 00:08:04,480
You've really outdone yourselves.

191
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,680
Beating up a beggar?

192
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:08,680
Er Ye.

193
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,279
We're just trying to help you out.

194
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,480
This beggar is way too bold.

195
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,800
He dared to steal from us.

196
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:16,439
Isn't this asking for trouble?

197
00:08:16,439 --> 00:08:17,160
What did he steal?

198
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,560
He stole a phoenix.

199
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,879
You beat him like this?

200
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:24,639
You guys,

201
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,720
Go settle the bill.

202
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,040
Get lost.

203
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:29,040
Er Ye.

204
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,160
Er Ye.

205
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,360
Alright, stop staring.

206
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,080
Go on, disperse.

207
00:08:45,639 --> 00:08:46,879
Who is it? What's going on?

208
00:08:46,879 --> 00:08:47,519
None of your business.

209
00:08:49,759 --> 00:08:50,799
What's wrong? You didn't touch the food.

210
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:52,279
Doesn't suit my taste.

211
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,159
It's fine.

212
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,039
If you're not eating, then leave.

213
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,360
Go quickly, I won't see you off.

214
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,159
What do you mean?

215
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:17,639
He's clinging on.

216
00:09:17,799 --> 00:09:18,360
Boss.

217
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,519
He insists on bowing to you in person.

218
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:21,919
Why bow?

219
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,679
Just give him some food.

220
00:09:23,679 --> 00:09:24,519
Let him leave quickly.

221
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,759
I told him, but he won't listen.

222
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:27,600
He insists on coming up.

223
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,320
I can't hold him back.

224
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,720
Boss.

225
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,200
If it weren't for you today,

226
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,919
I'd have lost my life here.

227
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:35,679
Thank you, you really are...

228
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,399
People weren't wrong about you.

229
00:09:37,639 --> 00:09:38,639
A living Bodhisattva.

230
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,840
Your great kindness,

231
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,720
I won't forget it.

232
00:09:41,159 --> 00:09:43,360
May your fortune fill Mada Mountain.

233
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:45,440
May your business reach Vladivostok.

234
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:56,840
Go mind your own business.

235
00:10:11,519 --> 00:10:12,320
Squad Leader.

236
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,200
Come in and talk.

237
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:22,480
Xiao Gui! Xiao Gui!

238
00:10:22,879 --> 00:10:24,159
Xiao Gui, it's really you!

239
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,240
Gui'er, you're still alive!

240
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,320
We all thought you were dead.

241
00:10:27,519 --> 00:10:28,039
Gui'er.

242
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,120
It's really you.

243
00:10:30,279 --> 00:10:30,799
Gui'er.

244
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:32,840
Gui'er.

245
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:36,240
What's with you guys?

246
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:37,440
Everyone's here.

247
00:10:38,399 --> 00:10:39,840
I'm not dreaming, am I?

248
00:10:41,279 --> 00:10:41,840
Don't just stand there.

249
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,480
Sit down.

250
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,200
Hurry, hurry.

251
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,080
Quick, sit down, sit down.

252
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,000
Hurry up.

253
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:46,240
Sit down quickly.

254
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,000
Come on.

255
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:50,799
Gui'er.

256
00:10:51,279 --> 00:10:52,120
What happened to your leg?

257
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:12,559
Uncle.

258
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:17,519
I finally found you all.

259
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,360
Don't cry, don't cry.

260
00:11:20,159 --> 00:11:21,120
It's good to see you.

261
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:22,799
Get up, get up.

262
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:23,879
Get up.

263
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:27,960
You must be hungry.

264
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,399
Eat something, go ahead.

265
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,320
Where's Sister Hua?

266
00:11:41,919 --> 00:11:42,879
Where's Little White Horse?

267
00:11:46,919 --> 00:11:48,440
Everyone who could come is here.

268
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,120
Those who didn't come...

269
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:51,759
...aren't with us anymore.

270
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,600
Xiao Gui.

271
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,600
What happened to your hand?

272
00:12:08,879 --> 00:12:09,360
Yeah.

273
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,279
How did it end up like this?

274
00:12:12,919 --> 00:12:13,759
Frozen, it's frozen.

275
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:15,639
It's frostbitten.

276
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:19,879
Gui'er.

277
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,080
You, you...

278
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,360
How did you find this place?

279
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:27,840
I...

280
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:32,120
I begged my way here.

281
00:12:37,519 --> 00:12:38,120
I...

282
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,279
I thought Mudanjiang

283
00:12:40,279 --> 00:12:41,159
was a big city.

284
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,360
Who would've thought...

285
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,000
Three days on the street,

286
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,080
I couldn't get a single bite.

287
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,639
People said

288
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,320
the boss of Tianhao Grand Restaurant

289
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,159
is a kind person.

290
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,240
So I came here.

291
00:12:57,039 --> 00:12:58,759
Didn't expect I'd almost get beaten to death.

292
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:02,799
Gui'er, why...

293
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,120
